# Drive Manifest Feed Structure

The drive manifest feed lives at topic `ph:v2:drive:<driveId>` and is owned by the drive creator's signer. Each feed index resolves to encrypted JSON on `/bytes`.

## Schema

```json
{
  "driveId": "drive-abc",
  "name": "Finance Drive",
  "documents": {
    "doc-001": {
      "documentType": "powerhouse/budget-statement",
      "name": "Q1 Budget",
      "parentFolder": "folder-reports",
      "lastUpdated": "2026-04-10T12:01:00Z"
    }
  },
  "folders": {
    "folder-reports": { "name": "Reports" }
  },
  "updatedAt": "2026-04-10T12:02:00Z"
}
```

## Role

- Indexes every document the drive contains and the folder tree
- `parentFolder` on a document lets clients reconstruct the folder hierarchy
- One drive manifest feed per drive, one feed index per update
